Exception Handling :Error detecting during execution are called exceptions.
                    use try,except,finally and else to handle exceptions.

else: Execute when no exception occour.
finally : it is always executed.

raise keyword :  it is used to raise an Exception/Error and stops the execution of the programs.
                  It is very useful when you want to work with the input validations.

with open statement : It is used when a pair of statements is to be executed with a block of code in between.

tell() : It is used to print the byte number at which the file pointer exists.
seek() : seek() method which enables us to modify the file pointer position externally.

OS module : This module provides us the functions that are involved in file processing operations
            like renaming, deleting, etc.

next(): It returns the next line from the file.
